A Republican strategy to counter Obama's re-election
The Republican leaders are justifying their policies with the need to combat electoral fraud.
However, the Brennan Center considers the latter to be a myth by reaffirming that electoral fraud in the US is more rare than the number of people killed by the flash.
Moreover, in 10 years, Republican lawyers have recorded only 300 cases of electoral fraud in the US.
One thing is certain: these new provisions will have a negative impact on voting participation.
